  "prompt": "What are some ways to microwave fish fingers?",
  "response": "Here are some ways to microwave fish fingers:\n\n1. Basic method:\n- Place fish fingers on a microwave-safe plate\n- Cook on high for 1-2 minutes\n- Turn halfway through cooking\n- Check they're piping hot before serving\n\n2. For crispier result:\n- Use a microwave crisper tray\n- Arrange fish fingers in a single layer\n- Microwave in short bursts, checking frequently\n- Let stand for 1 minute after cooking\n\n3. Wrapped method:\n- Wrap fish fingers in microwave-safe paper towel\n- This can help absorb excess moisture\n- Cook for 1-1.5 minutes on high\n\n4. Multiple fish fingers:\n- Arrange in a circular pattern\n- Leave space between them\n- Cook for 2-3 minutes, turning halfway\n- Ensure they reach 75\u00b0C (165\u00b0F) internal temperature\n\nTips:\n- Cooking times vary by microwave wattage\n- Always check package instructions\n- Avoid overcooking to prevent dryness\n- Let stand for a minute after cooking\n- Use a food thermometer to check temperature\n\nRemember, microwaving might not give as crispy a result as oven-baking.",
